FBIS4-15281 "drsov068__a94004" FBIS-SOV-94-068-A Daily Report 8 April 1994 ANNEX Russia National Affairs Finance Problems Force Russian TV To Cut Broadcasts Finance Problems Force Russian TV To Cut Broadcasts LD0404163794 Moscow RIA in English 1718 GMT 1 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD0404163794 Moscow RIA English BFN [Text] Moscow, April 1, RIA -- From April 1 considerable changes will be made in the principles used in drawing up weekly schedules of Russia Television programmes. Due to financial difficulties the length of broadcasting will be cut back by 2.5 hours daily -- at the expense of repeating feature films and political programmes in the daytime. The children's "Holiday Every Day" evening fairy-tale is moved from 19.45 to 18.40. Theatre programmes that appeared on Saturdays at 18.15 are to be shown on Tuesdays at 21.25.
